### English Title:
Trump's Tariff Decision Takes Effect, Affecting 60 Countries

### English Text Summary:
President Donald Trump's decision to impose tariffs on approximately 60 countries came into effect at 5 AM GMT on Wednesday. This decision is part of Trump's broader global tariff strategy, which includes higher import taxes on what he calls the "worst trade violators," particularly targeting China with tariffs exceeding 100% on some goods. China has responded by accusing Trump of bullying and has refused to eliminate its retaliatory tariffs. The global markets have lost trillions due to investor reactions to the uncertainty. South Korea has announced emergency support for its automotive sector, while Taiwan activated a stabilization fund to calm its market.

